  <strong>Trying a New Weird Keyboard</strong></br>
   I picked up a <a href="https://www.zsa.io/voyager">ZSA Voyager</a>, with the idea of having a nicer mechanical keyboard for travel. I'm definitely in the awkward-new-layout phase with it now. I'm fat fingering a lot of things and realizing that I don't have the muscle memory to get to various symbols. It's a smaller layout than I'm used to (my main work keyboard is a ErgoDox EZ), which is making for a steep learning curve. I'm typing this update on it right now and it's been a bit of a challenge. I remember getting use to the ErgoDox being pretty tricky but now it feels really natural, so I'll stick with it and keep messing with my layout.
