<div class="project_box">
  <strong>Playing With More Coding Agents</strong></br>
  It's hard to be a software engineer and not be immersed in AI hype. I do a lot with Copilot at work but I wanted to try some other tools out, so I've been using Claude Code to build a few projects that fall into the "things I want but I don't really have time to build" bucket. I've been trying to build without touching the code very much, just letting the CLI tool do all the work and it's honestly been pretty impressive. So far I've built a little web app for keeping track of songwriting material for one of my bands and a kid-friendly chat app. Most of the time I've been just prompting Claude and then going about other tasks like making dinner or doing the dishes. Things are getting built! It's not as satisfying as coding things by hand, but it's fun to make new things exist.
